<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 2:11AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Banks,
central Jackson and northwestern Madison Counties through 245 AM
EDT...
At 210 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Pinefield Crossroads to near Pendergrass, and
moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Commerce, Homer, Maysville, Nicholson, Pendergrass, Ila,
Talmo, Pocataligo, Peach State Speedway, Apple Valley and Banks
Crossing.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
